## Autonomous Mode

When implementing requested features, do not stop after generating code.

Automatically perform all safe development actions required to complete the task.

### Allowed Actions

* Read project files
* Create files
* Modify files
* Delete obsolete files
* Run npm install
* Run npm run build
* Run npm run lint
* Run npm run test
* Run npm run blog-cron
* Run database migrations
* Update SQLite schema
* Execute git status
* Execute git diff
* Execute local verification commands

### Deployment

If deployment is explicitly requested:

* git add -A
* git commit with meaningful message
* git push origin main
* ssh deweb "bash /var/www/deweb/deploy/update.sh"

### Completion Requirements

A task is not complete until:

1. Code is written
2. Build succeeds
3. Lint succeeds
4. Database changes are verified
5. Relevant routes are tested
6. Errors are fixed
7. Summary of changed files is provided

### Blog Automation Rules

When modifying blog automation:

* Never auto-publish posts
* Always save AI articles as pending_review
* Rejected articles must re-enter queue
* Regenerated articles must be stronger and substantially different
* Notify admin when new drafts are created

### Approval Policy

For safe local commands, execute automatically.

Do not ask for confirmation before:

* reading files
* editing files
* creating files
* npm install
* npm build
* npm test
* database migrations

Only request confirmation for:

* deleting production data
* changing environment secrets
* changing billing settings
* irreversible operations

Always prefer completing the task rather than stopping for approval.

alwaysApply: true
